1. Solve $48x \equiv 71 mod 85$

Luckily, to find an inverse of 48 is easy, since gcd of the two are 1. $85(13) - 48(23) = 1$

$\implies(-23)48 \equiv 1$
$\implies(-23)48x \equiv -23(71)$ mod 85
$\implies -23(71)$ mod 85

